cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on programming a collaborative robot by demonstration and learning contact-intensive tasks. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the framework uses only visual perception of the demonstrated task to learn the task. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as the framework uses reinforcement learning to tune the skill parameters. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also possible as the framework involves learning from a single training example and using self-evaluation to refine the model. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the intuitive nature of humans programming a collaborative robot by demonstration.
